---
name: Prime modulus binomial theorem
traditional: Fermat's little theorem
alternate:
 - Prime modulus unit remainder theorem
 - Prime modulus identity theorem
---

# Prime modulus binomial theorem

The traditional name "Fermat's little theorem" is amusing but totally unrelated to substance.  "Prime modulus binomial theorem" describes the substance of the proof more than it does the substance of the statement of the theorem, while the alternate names do vice-versa.
